description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a strong and experienced leader to become the manager at our Community Equipment Store in Scunthorpe. Based on site you will be responsible for all aspects of the day to day management of the Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Community Equipment Store provides and collects equipment and wheelchairs into people’s homes and local hospitals. It manages the procurement, repair, reconditioning and decontamination of equipment and wheelchairs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Equipment Store Manager will provide line management for the store staff, liaising with the workshop Lead Technician and the Store Lead, on occasions you will provide leadership and support in other areas of the store. You will ensure close liaison with patients, clinicians and other staff members . This role is central to facilitating a high standard of patient care and maintaining safe effective equipment and wheelchairs which is provided in an efficient timely manner. They have a central role in supporting the procurement of core and non-stock items, monitoring the departmental spend and ordering equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Darren Bartlett, Store Manager Assisted Living Centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Darren.bartlett@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;03033303297&lt;/p&gt;
